<br>
Realistically, the truth lies somewhere in the middle. <br>
<br>
Monopolies, Bad. Oligopolies, Bad. True Competition Good.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, all too often things are done in the name of capitalism/free markets that are really bad for competition, which is really what makes capitalism thrive. Waaaay too many mergers going on in the world these days. As soon as companies have to start competing on price, they start looking to eliminate their competitors so they can inflate their prices again. Some controls are needed to prevent the greed of capitalism from doing more harm than good. Some greed can be a good thing, and greed is generally rewarded under such a system.<br>
<br>
By the same token, Socialism would work pretty well if we were ants, but since we're humans, it tends to fail due to the fact that it does in fact reward laziness. Raz is correct that some good has come of socialism. If it didn't have some good ideas, no one would believe in it at all. Universal health care is a wonderful concept, I just can't trust a government to run things efficiently enough for it to actually be a help to everyone. Labor unions and civil service provide too many loopholes for inneffective and unmotivated workers to retain their employment. <br>
<br>
We're all born equal, after that, its up to you..... <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929"> Naladini </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
