<br>
Thats right, I knew I was missing something...  Your absolutely right Balanz, but this is because Socialism is a system/ideal that is a its absolute core a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>moral</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and good hearted ideal.  I honestly believe that most Socialists, who truely believe in the ideal of Socialism are extremely good hearted people.  Thus, they are ironically the leaders of Civil Rights movements, Labor movements (championing the downtrodden), and other such good hearted and noble objectives.  When you get down to the cold functionality of the viability of the system they advocate, it simply does not work.  <br>
<br>
