Anyway...I hate to do this to you Silverblade but the way I see it, Capitalism is the ONLY viable socio-economic system.  Capitalism is an ancient system that has survived centuries.  From its conception at the hands of Adam Smith in his book <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> The Wealth of Nations </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, Capitalism has flourished throughout Europe and the rest of Europe.  It has survived the Cold War, the great battle between Socialism and Capitalism, and it survives and thrives to this day.  <br>
<br>
So, because its lasted so long and its the system that everyone uses, that means its the BEST system, right?<br>
<br>
@#%$ no, well actually, it is the best system, but not for narrow-minded reasons like that.<br>
<br>
As I said in my last post, Human beings are greedy and self-motivated.  Capitalism works because it actually addresses these fallacys and accomodates them, something that Socialism unfortunatly does not.   <br>
<br>
Capitalism at inital glance is a cold hearted, sunovabitch, cruel-ass system.  I mean, @#%$, theoretically under Capitalism you can (and do) have starving kids and who cares?  Not my problem, your problem.  Thats the core theory of Capitalism, everyone looks out for numero uno (thats number one in spanish) and for some reason, an &quot;invisible hand&quot; magically appears out of nowhere and the economy and society as a whole advances all wrapped up in a nice little package.  <br>
<br>
Yep, thats pretty much Capitalism in a nutshell...  <br>
<br>
However, under Capitalism, people have a tangible motivator to work hard and advance.  People with skill, talent, and drive are motivated to work hard and create wealth for themselves.  Also, because under Capitalism, the market, instead of being controlled by the Government, is instead controlled by the Consumer, quality of goods, and thus standard of living as a whole goes up. <br>
<br>
Thus, while there is a greater econmoic diversity between rich and poor under Capitalism, the economy and the standard of living, as a whole is much better then what would be experienced under Socialism.  To grossly simplify my arguement, on a scale of 1 to 10 with 1 being starving and 10 being filthy (@#%$ you Bill Gates and your Demon Inspired, God Cursed, Soul Stealing,........DRUIDISH!!!!!!!!!, X-Box..thats right you X-Box Junkies, God is on MY side as he is on the side of all PS2 fans.....(i'm tired, don't take that seriously) ) .. rich<br>
